@startuml UC-02_Create_Workflow_Sequence

title UC-02: Create Workflow - Sequence Diagram

skinparam SequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #7B1FA2
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F3E5F5
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF9C4

actor User
participant Frontend
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant WorkflowService
participant Database as DB
participant AnalyticsService
participant ValidationService

User -> Frontend: 1. Click "New Workflow"
Frontend -> User: 2. Display Workflow Creation Form
User -> Frontend: 3. Enter Workflow Name
Frontend -> ValidationService: 4. validate_name(name)
ValidationService --> Frontend: 5. Name valid (3-100 chars)

User -> Frontend: 6. Enter Description (optional)
User -> Frontend: 7. Select Category/Tags
User -> Frontend: 8. Click Create

Frontend -> API: 9. POST /api/v1/workflows/create
note right of API
  Body: {
    "name": "Email Newsletter",
    "description": "...",
    "category": "marketing",
    "tags": ["email", "newsletter"]
  }
end note

API -> WorkflowService: 10. create_workflow(user_id, workflow_data)

WorkflowService -> ValidationService: 11. Validate workflow data
ValidationService --> WorkflowService: 12. All validations passed

WorkflowService -> DB: 13. INSERT Workflow Collection
activate DB
DB --> WorkflowService: 14. workflow_id returned
deactivate DB

WorkflowService -> DB: 15. Store Initial Metadata
activate DB
DB --> WorkflowService: 16. Metadata stored
deactivate DB

WorkflowService -> AnalyticsService: 17. Track Event("workflow_created")
AnalyticsService -> DB: 18. Store Analytics Event
DB --> AnalyticsService: 19. Event stored

WorkflowService --> API: 20. Return {workflow_id, status: "draft"}
API --> Frontend: 21. 201 Created + workflow_id
Frontend --> User: 22. Show Success Message
Frontend -> User: 23. Redirect to Workflow Canvas

note right of User
  Workflow now in DRAFT status
  - Can be edited
  - Cannot be executed yet
  - Auto-save every 30 seconds
end note

User -> Frontend: 24. (Optional) Enter Workflow Builder
Frontend -> API: 25. GET /api/v1/workflows/{workflow_id}
API -> WorkflowService: 26. get_workflow(workflow_id, user_id)
WorkflowService -> DB: 27. Fetch workflow
DB --> WorkflowService: 28. Return workflow data
WorkflowService --> API: 29. Workflow object
API --> Frontend: 30. 200 OK + workflow
Frontend --> User: 31. Load Canvas with workflow

@enduml
